(1) This finder-like view shows the files and folders with their sizes.\
(2) The treemap shows the files and folders in a way that should easily made clear which files and folders occupy most of the space. The selection in the finder-like view and the treemap is synchronized. (Please read (4) for the meaning of the different colors.)\
(3) Here some information is displayed about the file pointed at in the treemap.\
(4) The file kind statistic informs about the count of files of a specific type and the sum of their sizes. The list is sorted by size in descending order. Each kind has a color which is also used in the treemap (2). The same color is used throughout all opened folders for each kind.\
\
Through the "View" menu you can choose whether you would like to view package contents, you can zoom into folders and some more things.\
